article.headline: Stony Brook 65, Colgate 59
article.story: HAMILTON, N.Y. (AP) -- Mitchell Beauford scored 20 points, including eight in the final 41 seconds, to lead Stony Brook to a 65-59 non-conference victory over Colgate Friday. Ricky Lucas contributed 18 points for Stony Brook's first game of the season. Colgate was paced by Jon Simon's 15-point effort in what was their opening game as well. Stony Brook shot 48 percent for the game, compared to 38 percent for the Raiders. Colgate's Dan Gentile hit a three-point basket to cut a 6-point Stony Brook lead in half with 0:58 left. Beauford answered 17 seconds later with a layup, pushing the lead back to five. A layup by Daniel Waddy got Colgate back within three with 0:33 left in the game. Beauford then connected on the first and second of six consecutive free throws to ice the game for the Seawolves. Stony Brook took an early 6-0 lead with second-chance points and layups, holding the lead until 9:38 left in the first half, when a layup by Kyle Chones put Colgate ahead 14-13. The lead changed hands four more times in the half, with the Raiders ultimately heading into the break up 24-19. Colgate opened the second half with a basket by Simon to go up by seven, their largest lead of the game, prompting Stony Brook to utilize a zone for most of the second half. The Seawolves responded to the switch by going on an 11-0 run over the next five minutes to take a 34-29 lead. The run was punctuated by four points for both Lucas and Beauford. The Raiders pulled to within two at 36-34 with just under 11 minutes remaining on a jumper by Trevaron Vinson, but Stony Brook countered with a 9-0 run to go up 45-34 with 7:16 left in the game. The Seawolves extended the lead to 15 at 55-40 with 4:21 left to play following four consecutive points by Lucas. An 11-0 Colgate run got the Raiders within four with 1:15 left in the game after a layup by Marc Daniels.
